rComments: Approachable and warm. Great readings and interesting assignments.

All around a very excellent professor! The assignments can be challenging, but Heba provides a lot of detailed feedback. You have to put in the effort though and really think about each assignment carefully. If you put in the work, it is a rewarding process.

I took Heba for 2 courses across two different semesters and will be taking my 3rd course with her this upcoming semester. The first course I took had weekly Zoom meetings while the second one did not. I much preferred meeting up with her because you saw how knowledgeable and personable she is which made me more at ease the second time around!

Heba is a wonderful teacher & very knowledgeable in her subject matter. She gives weekly readings, is open to feedback and is very personable. Material is BIPOC focused. That being said, you cannot speak freely in her class. Heba is great, but attracts passionate individuals who do not accept any answer other than a "I concur!"

The entire course was just the prof posting readings with no explanation. The course syllabus did not even have topics. The assignments did not make sense. She does not reply to emails unless sent multiple times. No clear directions even when asking for assistance. This is my third degree and have never experienced this or have dropped a course.

Heba is one of the most exceptional professors at uOttawa. The assignments are challenging, which makes sense for a grad course, and she provides great feedback. She makes herself accessible and wants every student to do well in her course. If you are looking to challenge your own scholarship and writing, she is the prof to support you.
